1
00:01:11,171 --> 00:01:12,131
More blood!

2
00:01:12,251 --> 00:01:15,211
Great. Keep coming.
Chuck, Terry, pump away.

3
00:01:15,371 --> 00:01:17,251
Don't be stingy.

4
00:01:17,411 --> 00:01:19,291
Watch that arm.
I can see that fake arm.

5
00:01:19,451 --> 00:01:21,011
Chase, keep that claw
really moving.

6
00:01:21,171 --> 00:01:22,971
Jeffrey, jam it on there
just like Freddy would.

7
00:01:23,131 --> 00:01:25,771
Good, good. And cut!
Print that, Gretchen.

8
00:01:30,451 --> 00:01:31,571
Chase, you're a genius.

9
00:01:31,691 --> 00:01:33,891
This makes his old claw look
like Mother Teresa's mitten.

10
00:01:34,051 --> 00:01:36,171
You better thank them.
They're very sensitive.

11
00:01:36,291 --> 00:01:38,091
Chuck, Terry, great blood.

12
00:01:38,211 --> 00:01:40,971
- Thank you very much.
- Some of our best work.

13
00:01:41,091 --> 00:01:42,771
Hey, monkey man,
want to see some neat stuff?

14
00:01:44,011 --> 00:01:45,491
Come on.

15
00:01:45,611 --> 00:01:46,811
It's only make-Believe.

16
00:01:46,931 --> 00:01:48,931
Marianne, I gotta go.

17
00:01:54,211 --> 00:01:55,331
Low bridge.

18
00:01:58,291 --> 00:02:02,051
Let's see if we can
scare the P.J.'S off Mommy.

19
00:02:05,011 --> 00:02:06,131
Hey, Heather.

20
00:02:14,811 --> 00:02:15,931
You hungry, Dylan?

21
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:24,000
Upcoming jump scare (Minor)
Gotcha.
It should have flexed more.

22
00:02:26,251 --> 00:02:28,691
I think the servos
got shorted out with blood.

23
00:02:28,851 --> 00:02:31,771
Well, take it apart,
pull it out...

24
00:02:31,891 --> 00:02:33,571
and insulate them
with some styro.

25
00:02:33,691 --> 00:02:35,531
The thing wasn't meant to be
submerged, for Pete's sake.

26
00:02:37,211 --> 00:02:38,651
I don't like that thing.

27
00:02:38,771 --> 00:02:40,251
That thing puts bread
on our table.

28
00:02:40,371 --> 00:02:42,211
Is it alive, Daddy?

29
00:02:42,331 --> 00:02:44,971
Heather,
you're in the next shot.

30
00:02:45,091 --> 00:02:48,091
State-Of-The-Art animatronics
with bio-Organic grafting.

31
00:02:48,211 --> 00:02:51,211
Bull tendons, nerve bundles
from a live Doberman.

32
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:10,000
Upcoming jump scare (Minor)
Must've have picked up a signal
from an eighties walkie-talkie.
- Sure it's off?
- It's off.

33
00:03:11,851 --> 00:03:14,971
Funny, it's warm...
just like a real hand.

34
00:03:18,931 --> 00:03:20,291
Oh, God.

35
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:26,000
Upcoming jump scare (Minor)
What the hell's going on here?
Cut the effects!

36
00:03:32,371 --> 00:03:35,811
Terry, where is it? Terry!

37
00:03:35,931 --> 00:03:37,451
Chuck, get off me!

38
00:03:38,251 --> 00:03:39,811
Heather, where is it?

39
00:03:39,931 --> 00:03:41,571
Chase, where the hell is it?

40
00:03:46,131 --> 00:03:47,411
Come on.

41
00:03:54,291 --> 00:03:55,531
What the fuck?!

42
00:04:09,211 --> 00:04:10,571
Earthquake. Come on.

43
00:04:16,651 --> 00:04:18,411
Mommy!

44
00:04:49,011 --> 00:04:50,011
What is that?

45
00:04:50,971 --> 00:04:52,651
Car alarms.

46
00:04:55,611 --> 00:04:56,931
You OK?

47
00:05:00,171 --> 00:05:01,291
You OK, chief?

48
00:05:03,211 --> 00:05:04,531
Honey, do you have a fever?

49
00:05:04,651 --> 00:05:05,971
Just another earthquake, Dylan.

50
00:05:06,091 --> 00:05:07,611
Getting kind of fun, huh?

51
00:05:07,731 --> 00:05:09,971
Daddy. Blood.

52
00:05:10,091 --> 00:05:12,211
It's nothing, guys.

53
00:05:12,331 --> 00:05:14,971
It's a scratch. Really.

54
00:05:15,091 --> 00:05:16,571
Where did you get that?

55
00:05:16,691 --> 00:05:18,971
I don't know. Picture, I guess.

56
00:05:19,091 --> 00:05:21,371
When it fell. It's no big deal.

57
00:05:21,491 --> 00:05:23,411
Put a bandage on it.

58
00:05:23,531 --> 00:05:24,811
Don't worry about it.

59
00:05:33,011 --> 00:05:34,091
Geologists at Cal Tech...

60
00:05:34,171 --> 00:05:36,451
have confirmed
this morning's aftershock...

61
00:05:36,531 --> 00:05:37,931
Do we have to watch that?

62
00:05:38,051 --> 00:05:39,371
...five-point-three
on the Richter scale.

63
00:05:39,491 --> 00:05:40,491
Thought you turned it on.

64
00:05:40,611 --> 00:05:42,331
It was strong enough
to cause further collapse...

65
00:05:42,451 --> 00:05:44,691
of the already badly damaged
parking structure...

66
00:05:44,811 --> 00:05:46,411
I'll turn it off.

67
00:05:46,531 --> 00:05:48,811
Officials say
that this is normal...

68
00:05:48,931 --> 00:05:51,051
following a quake
of last week's magnitude...

69
00:05:51,171 --> 00:05:53,771
now thought to be a massive 6.8.

70
00:05:55,531 --> 00:05:58,571
Dylan, this is breakfast,
not arts and crafts.

71
00:06:00,451 --> 00:06:01,611
What?

72
00:06:01,731 --> 00:06:03,571
Did you get any sleep
last night?

73
00:06:03,691 --> 00:06:05,851
More or less.

74
00:06:05,971 --> 00:06:08,771
OK, time to get dressed.
I'm late.

75
00:06:08,891 --> 00:06:10,531
You going away?

76
00:06:10,651 --> 00:06:12,811
Just for a few hours.
Julie will be with you.

77
00:06:18,851 --> 00:06:21,771
Is there anything other than
the obvious bothering you?

78
00:06:21,891 --> 00:06:24,291
I think five earthquakes
in three weeks is enough.

79
00:06:26,571 --> 00:06:28,011
Hasn't been another phone call,
has there?

80
00:06:30,411 --> 00:06:32,491
Good sign.

81
00:06:32,611 --> 00:06:35,771
Two full weeks without him.
Maybe he got hit by a truck.

82
00:06:35,891 --> 00:06:38,411
He's closer, if anything.

83
00:06:38,531 --> 00:06:40,851
It's giving me nightmares,
Chase.

84
00:06:41,971 --> 00:06:43,331
Did you have one last night?

85
00:06:45,131 --> 00:06:47,291
It's just the earthquakes,
Heather.

86
00:06:47,411 --> 00:06:48,771
Maybe.

87
00:06:49,971 --> 00:06:51,931
Maybe I shouldn't do
this interview today.

88
00:06:52,051 --> 00:06:56,971
No. You gotta get back
on the horse sometime.

89
00:06:57,091 --> 00:07:00,251
Look, you had a nut case
making harassing phone calls.

90
00:07:00,371 --> 00:07:01,691
I know how scary that's been.

91
00:07:01,811 --> 00:07:03,571
No, you don't.

92
00:07:05,171 --> 00:07:08,091
OK, I don't.

93
00:07:08,211 --> 00:07:10,491
But it doesn't mean
that it can't be over.

94
00:07:10,611 --> 00:07:12,171
But what if it isn't over?

95
00:07:14,451 --> 00:07:16,251
Maybe you should
tell me your dream.

96
00:07:17,971 --> 00:07:20,011
It was nothing. I was...

97
00:07:21,811 --> 00:07:24,571
you and I were working on
this movie, together for once...

98
00:07:24,691 --> 00:07:28,091
and one of your special effects
went really wrong.

99
00:07:28,211 --> 00:07:32,411
And Chuck and Terry got hurt...

100
00:07:32,531 --> 00:07:33,571
and...

101
00:07:34,931 --> 00:07:36,691
well, your fingers were cut.

102
00:07:36,811 --> 00:07:38,091
Right here?

103
00:07:41,491 --> 00:07:44,451
Heather, you were
probably half awake...

104
00:07:44,571 --> 00:07:46,491
and saw my fingers get nicked
when the mirror fell.

105
00:07:46,611 --> 00:07:48,131
Dreams are like that.

106
00:07:52,331 --> 00:07:55,971
Look, if you don't want me
to go on this job, I won't.

107
00:07:58,251 --> 00:07:59,931
Just be careful, OK?

108
00:08:00,051 --> 00:08:02,611
I think I can survive
two days in Palm Springs...

109
00:08:02,731 --> 00:08:05,491
supplying soap bubbles
for a detergent commercial.

110
00:08:05,611 --> 00:08:06,611
I guess so.

111
00:08:06,731 --> 00:08:07,851
You guess so?

112
00:08:08,731 --> 00:08:09,771
Come here.

113
00:08:19,211 --> 00:08:20,691
Forty-eight hours.

114
00:08:22,131 --> 00:08:23,731
I'll be back in no time.

115
00:08:24,811 --> 00:08:25,971
I gotta go.

116
00:08:35,051 --> 00:08:36,491
I love what you've done
with the place.

117
00:08:37,931 --> 00:08:39,051
Knock 'em dead.

118
00:08:42,611 --> 00:08:44,731
Dylan, I gotta go.
Take care of Mommy.

119
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:08,000
Upcoming jump scare (Minor)
Nancy.

120
00:09:17,011 --> 00:09:19,331
Dylan, I don't want you
watching this.

121
00:09:23,091 --> 00:09:25,091
Dylan, what's wrong?
What's wrong?!

122
00:09:25,211 --> 00:09:26,531
What's happening to you?

123
00:09:41,651 --> 00:09:43,771
One, two...

124
00:09:57,011 --> 00:09:58,251
Freddy's coming for you!

125
00:10:11,891 --> 00:10:14,451
Someone's coming.

126
00:10:14,571 --> 00:10:15,571
What?

127
00:10:31,771 --> 00:10:33,011
Are you OK, honey?

128
00:10:50,411 --> 00:10:51,491
Is everything OK?

129
00:10:51,651 --> 00:10:54,411
It's just these quakes.
Did you feel one just now?

130
00:10:54,571 --> 00:10:57,211
No. A big truck went by
before you opened the door.

131
00:10:57,371 --> 00:10:58,971
It's life on the fault line.

132
00:10:59,131 --> 00:11:00,931
- Hey, tiger.
- Hi, Julie.

133
00:11:02,331 --> 00:11:05,371
Does he feel warm to you?
He had a fever this morning.

134
00:11:07,291 --> 00:11:08,491
No, he seems OK.

135
00:11:10,011 --> 00:11:11,571
Are you sure
that's all that's wrong?

136
00:11:14,651 --> 00:11:16,691
Leave us alone,
you son of a bitch!

137
00:11:16,851 --> 00:11:18,411
L.A. Limousine, ma'am.

138
00:11:18,571 --> 00:11:20,571
Just wanted you to know
I'm out front.

139
00:11:27,771 --> 00:11:29,931
I'm sorry.
Can you hang on a minute?

140
00:11:40,171 --> 00:11:41,411
What is it?

141
00:11:41,571 --> 00:11:42,571
I don't know.

142
00:11:44,091 --> 00:11:46,011
I just have
this weird feeling today.

143
00:11:46,171 --> 00:11:49,131
Mommy? Stay home, then.

144
00:11:55,571 --> 00:11:57,211
This damn caller.

145
00:11:59,931 --> 00:12:01,051
He's started again?

146
00:12:02,731 --> 00:12:04,371
Sick fuck.

147
00:12:05,531 --> 00:12:06,531
Sorry.

148
00:12:08,531 --> 00:12:11,331
Dylan doesn't seem
to have a fever.

149
00:12:11,451 --> 00:12:13,691
It's probably just your nerves.

150
00:12:13,851 --> 00:12:15,251
Nerves?

151
00:12:16,451 --> 00:12:19,171
I just meant from the shaker
this morning.

152
00:12:19,291 --> 00:12:21,411
Everybody's freaked out about
how many we've been having.

153
00:12:21,531 --> 00:12:23,011
And then these phone calls.

154
00:12:27,811 --> 00:12:28,931
Don't answer it.

155
00:12:37,691 --> 00:12:40,891
Excuse me, ma'am,
but we are going to be late.

156
00:12:52,371 --> 00:12:56,491
Dylan, I gotta go. Forgive me?

157
00:12:56,651 --> 00:12:57,771
Bye.

158
00:13:11,771 --> 00:13:13,411
I'll call the cops for you.

159
00:13:13,531 --> 00:13:14,651
You've got the number
on the fridge, right?

160
00:13:14,811 --> 00:13:16,291
Give them
the time they called...

161
00:13:16,411 --> 00:13:18,771
and they're keeping this list,
supposedly.

162
00:13:18,931 --> 00:13:21,371
Julie, I'm really sorry.

163
00:13:21,531 --> 00:13:23,331
My nerves are
a little raw these days.

164
00:13:23,451 --> 00:13:24,491
It's OK.

165
00:13:31,571 --> 00:13:32,771
Yeah. I gotta go.

166
00:13:32,891 --> 00:13:34,771
- Morning.
- Good morning.

167
00:13:49,691 --> 00:13:50,731
You played that girl.

168
00:13:52,491 --> 00:13:54,211
In that movie.

169
00:13:54,331 --> 00:13:55,691
With the guy with the...

170
00:13:56,891 --> 00:13:59,731
Yeah, sure. That's you.

171
00:13:59,851 --> 00:14:01,891
That's what I love
about this job.

172
00:14:02,011 --> 00:14:03,491
I get to meet the stars.

173
00:14:03,611 --> 00:14:05,571
I'm hardly a star.

174
00:14:05,691 --> 00:14:07,291
What, are you kidding?

175
00:14:07,411 --> 00:14:09,331
I love your stuff.

176
00:14:10,651 --> 00:14:11,931
The first was the best.

177
00:14:12,611 --> 00:14:15,491
Where the girlfriend's cut open
and dragged across the ceiling.

178
00:14:15,611 --> 00:14:16,611
It was awesome.

179
00:14:16,731 --> 00:14:20,451
And when all that blood comes
out of your boyfriend's bed?

180
00:14:20,571 --> 00:14:22,211
I thought I'd shit.

181
00:14:22,331 --> 00:14:24,771
But they never should
have killed off Freddy.

182
00:14:25,931 --> 00:14:27,451
Heather, look, we gotta go.

183
00:14:27,571 --> 00:14:30,851
Cutting it close, aren't you?
You trying to get me fired?

184
00:14:30,971 --> 00:14:32,331
OK! We're coming!

185
00:14:35,411 --> 00:14:37,931
So, Heather, we're approaching
the tenth anniversary...

186
00:14:38,051 --> 00:14:39,531
of this whole
"Nightmare on Elm Street" thing.

187
00:14:39,651 --> 00:14:42,891
I mean, the original,
five very popular sequels.

188
00:14:43,011 --> 00:14:46,811
How has all the success
affected you personally?

189
00:14:47,931 --> 00:14:50,371
I don't know
if it really has, Sam.

190
00:14:50,491 --> 00:14:52,531
God. With the exception
of One and Three...

191
00:14:52,651 --> 00:14:54,331
I pretty much stayed out of it.

192
00:14:54,451 --> 00:14:56,371
Well, I'm doing a lot more
television now...

193
00:14:57,000 --> 00:15:02,000
Upcoming jump scare (Minor)
so those hours
let me spend a lot more time...
with my husband
and my little boy.
You have a little boy.
What's his name?

194
00:15:02,971 --> 00:15:03,971
Dylan.

195
00:15:04,091 --> 00:15:06,611
With Dylan,
does that change your feeling...

196
00:15:06,731 --> 00:15:08,771
your perspective
about horror movies?

197
00:15:08,891 --> 00:15:10,451
No, not really.

198
00:15:10,571 --> 00:15:12,331
Would you let him
see one of your movies?

199
00:15:12,451 --> 00:15:14,371
My son? No.

200
00:15:14,491 --> 00:15:16,691
I'm sure people ask you this
all the time...

201
00:15:16,811 --> 00:15:19,011
Is there going
to be another sequel...

202
00:15:19,131 --> 00:15:22,571
and what's more,
is Freddy really dead?

203
00:15:22,691 --> 00:15:25,211
Of course he is.
Freddy's dead and gone.

204
00:15:25,331 --> 00:15:28,771
And how about your co-Star
in the original...

205
00:15:28,891 --> 00:15:31,091
would you trust him
alone with Dylan?

206
00:15:31,211 --> 00:15:33,731
Robert? I don't know.

207
00:15:33,851 --> 00:15:35,851
Why don't we ask him
how he'd feel about it?

208
00:15:35,971 --> 00:15:39,211
We've got a big surprise for you
and for our audience.

209
00:15:39,331 --> 00:15:41,211
Let's bring him out.
He is the best of the bad.

210
00:15:41,331 --> 00:15:44,131
Let's say hello
to Robert Englund.

211
00:15:53,371 --> 00:15:55,491
Love ya, babe!

212
00:15:55,611 --> 00:15:57,011
We'll do lunch!

213
00:16:00,611 --> 00:16:03,491
I'm alive once again!

214
00:16:03,611 --> 00:16:07,571
Freddy's back! Give it up
for your Uncle Freddy!

215
00:16:08,891 --> 00:16:12,091
Just when you thought it was
safe to get back into bed!

216
00:16:15,571 --> 00:16:16,691
Give me five!

217
00:16:21,051 --> 00:16:24,611
I'm back,
and I'm badder than ever!

218
00:16:28,451 --> 00:16:31,931
You are all my children now!

219
00:16:38,331 --> 00:16:39,491
I got to go, Robert.

220
00:16:39,611 --> 00:16:42,051
Just a second. I'll walk you.

221
00:16:42,171 --> 00:16:43,531
There you go, kids.

222
00:16:43,651 --> 00:16:45,131
- Thank you.
- Bye-Bye.

223
00:16:46,531 --> 00:16:48,411
- You OK?
- I'm fine.

224
00:16:48,531 --> 00:16:50,891
Well, everything went great,
I thought.

225
00:16:51,011 --> 00:16:52,611
We really got you, didn't we?

226
00:16:52,731 --> 00:16:54,531
I don't know why
you didn't tell me.

227
00:16:54,651 --> 00:16:57,731
Come on. They loved
the expression on your face.

228
00:16:57,851 --> 00:16:59,171
I think they'd like
to see us together again.

229
00:16:59,291 --> 00:17:01,211
In what, a romantic comedy?

230
00:17:01,331 --> 00:17:02,651
Just because
it's a love story...

231
00:17:02,771 --> 00:17:05,571
doesn't mean you can't
have a decapitation or two.

232
00:17:05,691 --> 00:17:08,491
- There's a call for you.
- For me?

233
00:17:08,611 --> 00:17:09,971
I'll talk to you later.

234
00:17:13,051 --> 00:17:15,891
Heather, it's Sara Risher
over at New Line Cinema.

235
00:17:16,011 --> 00:17:17,211
How are you?

236
00:17:17,331 --> 00:17:19,851
How are you?
This is a voice from the past.

237
00:17:19,971 --> 00:17:20,971
It sure is.

238
00:17:21,091 --> 00:17:23,091
Listen, Heather,
I won't take but a minute.

239
00:17:23,211 --> 00:17:25,451
It's just that we have
something to propose to you...

240
00:17:25,571 --> 00:17:27,491
and I wonder
if you'd stop by the offices.

241
00:17:27,611 --> 00:17:29,371
Bob would love to talk to you.

242
00:17:29,491 --> 00:17:30,531
Sure. When?

243
00:17:30,651 --> 00:17:33,131
No time like the present.
The car will bring you over.

244
00:17:33,251 --> 00:17:34,851
- Now?
-Just take a minute.

245
00:17:34,971 --> 00:17:37,371
You'll be glad you did, I bet.
Bye.

246
00:18:01,051 --> 00:18:03,571
- Can I help you?
- I'm here to see Bob Shaye.

247
00:18:03,691 --> 00:18:05,171
Was Bob expecting you?

248
00:18:06,891 --> 00:18:08,051
Sara. How are you?

249
00:18:08,171 --> 00:18:10,371
- I'm fine. How are you?
- Great to see you.

250
00:18:10,491 --> 00:18:12,291
- You look great.
- Thank you.

251
00:18:12,411 --> 00:18:15,331
Bob is dying to see you.
Can I get you something?

252
00:18:15,451 --> 00:18:17,011
- Coffee would be fine.
- Black?

253
00:18:17,131 --> 00:18:19,011
- Black's fine.
- Could you get us some coffee?

254
00:18:19,131 --> 00:18:20,331
- Sure.
- Thanks.

255
